Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler to high. Roughly chop @thyme{¼%ounce} leaves. Roughly chop @walnuts{1%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine walnuts and half the @Parmesan cheese{½%cup}. Stir in @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cut @eggplant{1} into ½-inch cubes. Cut @zucchini{1} into 2-inch lengths, then cut each piece into thin wedges.

Toss eggplant and zucchini on #baking sheet{} with a pinch of salt, a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} and @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon} (to taste—it's spicy). Broil until tender and lightly browned, ~{10-12%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

Strip thyme leaves from stems; discard stems. Place thyme leaves, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @milk{1%cup}, @water{1%cup} and @butter{2%tbsp} in a #medium pot{}. Bring to a gentle boil over medium-high heat, then lower heat and reduce to a simmer. Stir in @polenta{½%cup}. Cook, stirring constantly, until polenta is thick and oozy, ~{5-7%minutes}. Stir in remaining Parmesan. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide polenta between #plates{}. Top with veggies and drizzle with walnut salsa.